@@ -0,0 +1,59 @@
+# Fix for Issue #2028: Do Not Merge Annotated Expression with Function Signature Rule
+
+## Problem Description
+
+The `function-signature` rule was merging annotated function body expressions with the function signature, even when the annotation contained parameters. This violated the `annotation` rule, which requires annotations with parameters to be on separate lines.
+
+### Example
+
+Original code:
+```kotlin
+private fun getErrorMessage(value: String): String =
+        @Suppress("DEPRECATION")
+        customMessage.takeUnless { it.isEmpty() } ?: String.format(DEFAULT_ERROR_MESSAGE_WITH_NO_REASON, value)
+```
+
+Before fix: The function-signature rule would merge the annotation with the signature, producing invalid output that violates the annotation rule.
+
+After fix: The annotation remains on a separate line, respecting both rules.
+
+## Solution
+
+Modified `FunctionSignatureRule.kt` to:
+
+1. **Added import**: `import com.pinterest.ktlint.rule.engine.core.api.ElementType.ANNOTATED_EXPRESSION`
+
+2. **Added helper methods**:
+   - `containsAnnotatedExpressionWithParameters()`: Checks if the function body expression contains an annotated expression with parameters
+   - `hasAnnotationWithValueArgumentList()`: Checks if a node has an annotation with value argument list
+   - `isAnnotationEntryWithValueArgumentList()`: Checks if an annotation entry has a value argument list
+
+3. **Modified merge logic**: In the `fixFunctionBodyExpression` method, added a check `!containsAnnotatedExpressionWithParameters(functionBodyExpressionNodes)` before merging:
+
+```kotlin
+val mergeWithFunctionSignature =
+    if (firstLineOfBodyExpression.length < maxLengthRemainingForFirstLineOfBodyExpression) {
+        !containsAnnotatedExpressionWithParameters(functionBodyExpressionNodes) &&
+            (functionBodyExpressionWrapping == default ||
+            (functionBodyExpressionWrapping == multiline && functionBodyExpressionLines.size == 1) ||
+            node.isMultilineFunctionSignatureWithoutExplicitReturnType(
+                lastNodeOfFunctionSignatureWithBodyExpression,
+            ))
+    } else {
+        false
+    }
+```
+
+## Files Changed
+
+- `ktlint-ruleset-standard/src/main/kotlin/com/pinterest/ktlint/ruleset/standard/rules/FunctionSignatureRule.kt`
+  - Added ANNOTATED_EXPRESSION import
+  - Added 3 helper methods to check for annotated expressions with parameters
+  - Modified mergeWithFunctionSignature logic to prevent merging when annotated expressions with parameters are present
+
+## Impact
+
+- The `function-signature` rule now respects the `annotation` rule by not merging function body expressions that contain annotations with parameters
+- Existing functionality is preserved for non-annotated expressions
+- The fix ensures that both rules can work together harmoniously without conflicts
+

